replies.body:
The same way I think anyone gets into it, just loved playing games. <3

I played a HEAP of games like most of my friends during high-school, but I also DM'ed a DnD game for about 5 years at the same time. During that time, the world-building, the story telling and modifying/messing with systems is probably what pushed me beyond just a player and to think, _"yeah, I wanna create experiences for people and watch them smile and have fun playing it"_. I think it's probably common across any creative industry, but it's super satisfying to make something and see people have a passionate reaction to what you've made.

Back when I started though, there were no dedicated 'game design' schools or any real clear pathways for 'how to break into the industry'. I just went to Japan with $3k in savings and YOLO'd it. It worked out, but not a recommended strat. ^_^;

1) While making Doom Bots we scrapped a Doom Ashe bot, but not before this bug happened. The idea for her Doom Crystal Arrow was that it would 'turn corners' and be homing. Yeah. :) So during one game Doom Ashe fires her arrow at someone, they flash dodge it, and it flies off bottom of screen. Phew.. safe. Then it re-enters from screen-right and nails him, like a cartoon. And then we scrapped Doom Ashe. ^.^;

2) Doom Bots was pretty fun. See above. :D

3) I'm playing _Final Fantasy 14_ atm, but I always come back to something PvP eventually. _Samurai Gunn_. So good. :)
